To force the Ray head node to use a custom SSH private key file to connect to the worker nodes, you can specify the `ssh_private_key` configuration option in the Ray head node configuration file.
Here is an example of how you can modify the Ray head node configuration file to use a custom SSH private key file:
```
{
"head_node_type": "ray.head.default",
"file_mounts": {
"# Files or directories to copy to the head and worker nodes. The format is a dictionary from REMOTE_PATH: LOCAL_PATH, e.g.
file_mounts: {
"~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub": "~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub",
"/path/to/your/custom/private_key.pem": "/path/to/your/custom/private_key.pem"
},
