}
```
In this example, the `ssh_private_key` configuration option is set to the path of the custom SSH private key file. This will cause the Ray head node to use this private key file to connect to the worker nodes instead of the default private key file.
Note that you will also need to make sure that the custom SSH private key file is in the Ray head node's `~/.ssh` directory and that the Ray head node has the necessary permissions to access the file.
